# MUI Component Styling Standards

## Context
- When implementing UI components using MUI
- When converting existing components to MUI
- When maintaining consistent styling across the application
- When customizing MUI components

## Critical Rules

### Component Structure
- Use MUI's Box component for layout and containers
- Use MUI's Typography for all text elements
- Use MUI's Grid or Box with flex for layouts
- Prefer direct styling over styled-components when possible

### Styling Approach
- Use sx prop for component-specific styles
- Define styles inline with the component for better maintainability
- Use theme colors and spacing when possible
- Follow the established color scheme:
  - Primary actions: #3ed6be
  - Hover states: Slightly darker (#2fcbb0)
  - Text colors: #2d3748 for main, #b0b7c3 for secondary
  - Backgrounds: #f8f9fa for page, #fafdfe for cards

### Layout Standards
- Use Box with flex for centering and alignment
- Maintain consistent spacing using MUI's spacing system
- Use proper breakpoints for responsive design
- Follow established border radius (borderRadius: 3)
- Use consistent shadows (boxShadow: '0 4px 24px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.04)')

### Form Components
- Use MUI TextField with custom styling
- Maintain consistent input heights (48px)
- Use consistent font sizes (15.5px for inputs)
- Apply proper spacing between form elements
- Include proper error states and messages

### Button Standards
- Use MUI Button component
- Apply consistent padding (py: 1.5)
- Use uppercase for button text
- Maintain consistent border radius (borderRadius: 3)
- Include hover states
- Show loading states when needed

## Examples

<example>
// Good: Proper MUI component styling
<Box
   sx={{
      width: 370,
      bgcolor: '#fafdfe',
      borderRadius: 3,
      boxShadow: '0 4px 24px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.04)',
      p: 4,
   }}
>
   <Typography
      variant="h5"
      sx={{
         color: '#3ed6be',
         fontSize: 36,
         fontWeight: 700,
         mb: 1,
      }}
   >
      Title
   </Typography>
   <TextField
      fullWidth
      sx={{
         bgcolor: '#fff',
         borderRadius: 3,
         '& .MuiOutlinedInput-root': {
            height: 48,
            fontSize: 15.5,
            color: '#2d3748',
            fontWeight: 500,
            '& fieldset': {
               borderColor: 'rgb(240, 240, 240)',
            },
         },
      }}
   />
   <Button
      fullWidth
      sx={{
         bgcolor: '#3ed6be',
         borderRadius: 3,
         fontWeight: 700,
         fontSize: 16,
         py: 1.5,
         textTransform: 'uppercase',
         '&:hover': { bgcolor: '#2fcbb0' },
      }}
   >
      Submit
   </Button>
</Box>
</example>

